## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="af8bd-102">Wystąpienie <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs> jest tworzone, gdy <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> obiektu zgłasza <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.EmulateRecognizeCompleted> zdarzeń.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="af8bd-102">An instance of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs> is created when the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> object raises the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.EmulateRecognizeCompleted> event.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="af8bd-103">Aby uzyskać informacje o wyniku rozpoznawania, dostęp do <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> właściwości programu obsługi zdarzenia.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="af8bd-103">To obtain information about the result of recognition, access the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> property in the handler for the event.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="af8bd-104">Emulacja polega na tekst, zamiast audio, to dane wejściowe do aparatu rozpoznawania mowy.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="af8bd-104">Emulation is the process by which text, instead of audio, is the input to a speech recognition engine.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="af8bd-105">Aby pominąć audio dane wejściowe dla <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> obiektu podczas emulacji, użyj <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SetInputToNull%2A> metody.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="af8bd-105">To bypass the audio inputs for a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> object during emulation, use the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SetInputToNull%2A> method.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="af8bd-106">Jeśli aparat rozpoznawania mowy napotkał wyjątek podczas operacji rozpoznawania <xref:System.ComponentModel.AsyncCompletedEventArgs.Error%2A> właściwość jest ustawiona na wyjątek i <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> właściwość jest ustawiona na `null`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="af8bd-106">If the speech recognition engine encounters an exception during the recognition operation, the <xref:System.ComponentModel.AsyncCompletedEventArgs.Error%2A> property is set to the exception and the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> property is set to `null`.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="af8bd-107"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs> pochodzi od klasy <xref:System.ComponentModel.AsyncCompletedEventArgs>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="af8bd-107"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs> derives from <xref:System.ComponentModel.AsyncCompletedEventArgs>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="af8bd-108">Poniższy przykład dodaje program obsługi zdarzeń dla <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.EmulateRecognizeCompleted> zdarzenia <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="af8bd-108">The following example adds an event handler for the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.EmulateRecognizeCompleted> event to a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="af8bd-109">Klauzula obsługi przejmie rozpoznany tekst z <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> właściwości.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="af8bd-109">The handler gets the recognized text from the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> property.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
private SpeechRecognitionEngine sre;  
  
// Initialize the speech recognition engine.   
private void Initialize()  
{  
  sre = new SpeechRecognitionEngine();  
  
  // Add a handler for the EmulateRecognizeCompleted event.  
  sre.EmulateRecognizeCompleted += new EventHandler<EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs>(sre_EmulateRecognizeCompleted);  
  
  // Add other initialization code here.  
}  
  
// Handle the EmulateRecognizeCompleted event.   
void sre_EmulateRecognizeCompleted(object sender, EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs e)  
{  
  if (e.Result == null) return;  
  
  string phrase = e.Result.Text;  
  
  // Add event handler code here.  
}  
  
```
